#+TITLE: Class 20 - Objections to Libet 
#+DATE: Monday November 7, 2016
#+SLUG: class20-legal
#+TAGS: free will, neuroscience, law, responsibility 
  
-------

Today we'll discuss some objections to Libet's argument as well as some
ramifications of our understanding of the neuroscience of action for
legal views of responsibility. 

* Readings
- Sinnott-Armstrong, [[file:{filename}/readings/SAOnLibet.pdf][Lessons from Libet]]
* Videos
- [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rCM5BFU01YU][Free Will and Neuroscience: Revisiting Libet's Experiments]]
